{"title":"Scroll of unholy creation","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Scroll_of_unholy_creation","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n| Type | Scroll                                                                                                              |\n| :--- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name | Scroll of unholy creation                                                                                           |\n| Icon | [![Scroll of unholy creation.png](/images/b/b3/Scroll_of_unholy_creation.png)](/File:Scroll_of_unholy_creation.png) |\n\n|   |                                                                                      |\n| - | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|   | This scroll draws unformed lumps of flesh from the Abyss to create a terrible beast. |\n\nReading a **scroll of unholy creation** will create a friendly, permanent [small abomination](/Small_abomination \"Small abomination\") to do your bidding. Unlike [derived undead](/Derived_undead \"Derived undead\"), they can heal over time and will follow you up and down [stairs](/Stairs \"Stairs\").\n\nIf you're worshipping a [good god](/Good_god \"Good god\"), the abomination will be hostile. The good gods also forbid its intentional use.\n\n## Strategy\n\nThese monsters can be useful allies in the early game, providing additional damage output and being able to survive for a few floors if handled with care. In the mid- and late-game, however, they are too fragile to be of much use.\n\n### Tips & Tricks\n\n- If you're worshipping a good god, the hostile abomination can be extremely dangerous in the early-game.\n\n  - [Zin](/Zin \"Zin\") - Reciting should destroy them with a few attempts. Reciting next to a small abomination is very dangerous early on, however, so try to get some distance between you and the abomination first.\n  - [The Shining One](/The_Shining_One \"The Shining One\") - If you have it, Cleansing Flame works just as well.\n\n- While monsters normally disregard scrolls, intelligent ones will use scrolls of unholy creation if they find them. Bear in mind this does provide a little bit of extra XP and possibly piety if you don't think you'll have a use for them yourself.\n\n## History\n\n- Scrolls of unholy creation were removed in [0.12](/0.12 \"0.12\").\n- Prior to [0.11](/0.11 \"0.11\"), these were known as **[scrolls of summoning](/Scrolls_of_summoning \"Scrolls of summoning\")**, but functioned identically. The item which now goes by that name functions very differently.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Scroll of unholy creation - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Scroll_of_unholy_creation\",\"wgTitle\":\"Scroll of unholy creation\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":74424,\"wgRevisionId\":74424,\"wgArticleId\":1464,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Obsolete articles\",\"Scroll\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",