search\">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div style=\"border: 1px solid #f00; background-color: #fcc; border-left: 15px solid #f00; margin-bottom: 20px; width: 100%; padding: 4px 10px; line-height: 1.1em; width: auto;\"><i><b>Obsolete</b>: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.</i></div>\n<div style=\"margin: 1.4em; margin-top:0; margin-right:0; padding: 0px; float: right; border:none;\">\n<table class=\"prettytable\" style=\"border:none; margin:0; padding:0; width:18em;\">\n\n<tr>\n<th align=\"left\"> Type\n</th>\n<td> Scroll\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"left\"> Name\n</th>\n<td> Scroll of unholy creation\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"left\"> Icon\n</th>\n<td> <a href=\"/File:Scroll_of_unholy_creation.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Scroll of unholy creation.png\" src=\"/images/b/b3/Scroll_of_unholy_creation.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</td></tr></table>\n</div>\n<table style=\"background:#f5faff; border:1px solid #cedff2; width:auto; margin: 0px 5%; margin-bottom:1.25em; font-style:italic; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:1.5em 1em;\">\n\n<tr>\n<td>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 100%;\"> This scroll draws unformed lumps of flesh from the Abyss to create a terrible beast.\n</td></tr></table>\n<p>Reading a <b>scroll of unholy creation</b> will create a friendly, permanent <a href=\"/Small_abomination\" title=\"Small abomination\">small abomination</a> to do your bidding. Unlike <a href=\"/Derived_undead\" title=\"Derived undead\">derived undead</a>, they can heal over time and will follow you up and down <a href=\"/Stairs\" title=\"Stairs\">stairs</a>.\n</p><p>If you're worshipping a <a href=\"/Good_god\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Good god\">good god</a>, the abomination will be hostile. The good gods also forbid its intentional use.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategy\">Strategy</span></h2>\n<p>These monsters can be useful allies in the early game, providing additional damage output and being able to survive for a few floors if handled with care. In the mid- and late-game, however, they are too fragile to be of much use. \n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Tips_.26_Tricks\">Tips &amp; Tricks</span></h3>\n<ul><li>If you're worshipping a good god, the hostile abomination can be extremely dangerous in the early-game.\n<ul><li><a href=\"/Zin\" title=\"Zin\">Zin</a> - Reciting should destroy them with a few attempts. Reciting next to a small abomination is very dangerous early on, however, so try to get some distance between you and the abomination first. </li>\n<li><a href=\"/The_Shining_One\" title=\"The Shining One\">The Shining One</a> - If you have it, Cleansing Flame works just as well.</li></ul></li>\n<li>While monsters normally disregard scrolls, intelligent ones will use scrolls of unholy creation if they find them. Bear in mind this does provide a little bit of extra XP and possibly piety if you don't think you'll have a use for them yourself.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2>\n<ul><li>Scrolls of unholy creation were removed in <a href=\"/0.12\" title=\"0.12\">0.12</a>.</li>\n<li>Prior to <a href=\"/0.11\" title=\"0.11\">0.11</a>, these were known as <b><a href=\"/Scrolls_of_summoning\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Scrolls of summoning\">scrolls of summoning</a></b>, but functioned identically. The item which now goes by that name functions very differently.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240916113013\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\n[SMW] In‐text annotation parser time: 0.002 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.036 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.215 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 38/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 172/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1056/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 